1
00:00:44,960 --> 00:00:45,559
Don't

2
00:00:46,920 --> 00:00:47,599
Don't

3
00:00:48,039 --> 00:00:48,719
Please don't hurt me.

4
00:00:52,039 --> 00:00:52,760
Oh dear.

5
00:00:53,480 --> 00:00:53,800
Hey.

6
00:00:54,320 --> 00:00:54,719
Kin.

7
00:00:55,199 --> 00:00:55,599
Kin.

8
00:00:56,519 --> 00:00:58,599
He's burning up.

9
00:00:59,320 --> 00:01:01,400
His fever must be dangerously high.

10
00:01:01,880 --> 00:01:02,719
What should we do?

11
00:01:03,360 --> 00:01:04,000
Oh boy...

12
00:01:05,559 --> 00:01:06,320
Oh, Kin...

13
00:01:11,000 --> 00:01:12,079
Let me ask you straight.

14
00:01:13,159 --> 00:01:14,639
What we're doing right now...

15
00:01:15,400 --> 00:01:16,400
is it really the right thing?

16
00:01:16,840 --> 00:01:17,280
Huh?

17
00:01:17,719 --> 00:01:19,119
Have you really thought this through?

18
00:01:20,000 --> 00:01:21,239
I think

19
00:01:22,000 --> 00:01:24,599
it's just like adding fuel to the fire."

20
00:01:24,960 --> 00:01:26,199
Pouring oil over it.

21
00:01:26,719 --> 00:01:27,639
Making the flames of vengeance

22
00:01:27,639 --> 00:01:29,599
burn even brighter, don't you think?

23
00:01:30,039 --> 00:01:30,840
Huh?

24
00:01:31,880 --> 00:01:33,239
Then what do you expect me to do

25
00:01:34,239 --> 00:01:35,400
Since

26
00:01:36,119 --> 00:01:37,000
Even the law

27
00:01:37,639 --> 00:01:39,119
can't do anything to people like them.

28
00:01:49,760 --> 00:01:50,440
Auntie.

29
00:01:50,639 --> 00:01:50,960
Yes?

30
00:01:53,320 --> 00:01:55,039
Saturn has caused trouble again.

31
00:01:55,400 --> 00:01:57,400
This time, someone actually died.

32
00:01:57,679 --> 00:01:58,199
Khaeng Khae.

33
00:01:58,440 --> 00:01:59,320
What on earth are you talking about?

34
00:02:00,320 --> 00:02:01,639
I'm telling the truth.

35
00:02:01,639 --> 00:02:03,159
The rumors are spreading everywhere

36
00:02:03,159 --> 00:02:04,920
that someone committed suicide over love.

37
00:02:05,280 --> 00:02:07,039
And Saturn is the root cause of it.

38
00:02:10,159 --> 00:02:10,519
Khaeng Khae.

39
00:02:11,440 --> 00:02:13,480
Go tell Lawyer Nod

40
00:02:13,840 --> 00:02:15,599
to do whatever it takes to put a stop to this.

41
00:02:16,079 --> 00:02:18,400
Don't let my grandson get
dragged into this case.

42
00:02:19,039 --> 00:02:21,599
Our family name must
not be tarnished, understood?

43
00:02:21,599 --> 00:02:22,280
Yes, Auntie.

44
00:02:23,280 --> 00:02:25,880
Lawyer Nod and I
will do everything in our power

45
00:02:26,440 --> 00:02:27,039
Saturn

46
00:02:27,039 --> 00:02:28,840
will definitely be cleared of this.

47
00:02:41,360 --> 00:02:42,559
Is he going to die?

48
00:02:42,559 --> 00:02:43,400
Oh, lord help me.

49
00:02:44,800 --> 00:02:45,639
I know, Auntie.

50
00:02:46,760 --> 00:02:47,719
That what I'm doing

51
00:02:48,440 --> 00:02:49,840
isn't going to make things any better.

52
00:02:52,000 --> 00:02:52,960
But it's still better than just

53
00:02:52,960 --> 00:02:54,079
sitting around doing nothing,

54
00:02:54,960 --> 00:02:56,840
and letting that murderer walk free.

55
00:02:57,760 --> 00:02:58,719
living the high life,

56
00:02:59,679 --> 00:03:01,960
and continuing to
ruin other people's lives.

57
00:03:08,760 --> 00:03:10,360
If that's how you really see it

58
00:03:10,840 --> 00:03:11,760
From now on

59
00:03:13,000 --> 00:03:13,760
I...

60
00:03:13,760 --> 00:03:14,639
this old lady right here

61
00:03:15,000 --> 00:03:15,840
is washing her hands of this.

62
00:03:16,239 --> 00:03:18,000
Do whatever you want. Go ahead.

63
00:03:18,079 --> 00:03:18,920
Just do it

64
00:03:19,800 --> 00:03:21,000
If you think

65
00:03:21,000 --> 00:03:24,119
if you think that killing him
will cure your vengeance,

66
00:03:24,119 --> 00:03:25,519
then go ahead and kill him.

67
00:03:26,480 --> 00:03:27,880
But once he's dead

68
00:03:28,360 --> 00:03:30,000
do me a favor and bury the body.

69
00:03:30,000 --> 00:03:31,280
Keep it out of my sight.

70
00:03:31,280 --> 00:03:33,239
Don't let this old woman
suffer the trouble

71
00:03:33,239 --> 00:03:34,559
of having to look at it.

72
00:03:34,559 --> 00:03:35,880
Just do it! Yeah.

73
00:03:46,079 --> 00:03:47,119
Please don't hurt me.

74
00:03:49,119 --> 00:03:50,440
I'm not Saturn.

75
00:03:57,679 --> 00:03:58,239
Don't.

76
00:03:59,039 --> 00:04:00,840
I beg you, please don't hurt me.

77
00:04:02,480 --> 00:04:04,199
I'm really not Saturn.

78
00:04:26,840 --> 00:04:27,480
Aunt Tammy.

79
00:04:28,039 --> 00:04:28,360
Yeah?

80
00:04:28,480 --> 00:04:29,880
I'm going to go get
some more firewood.

81
00:04:29,880 --> 00:04:30,280
Alright

82
00:04:30,599 --> 00:04:31,559
Keep an eye on him for me.

83
00:04:31,800 --> 00:04:32,599
Don't let him escape.

84
00:04:33,280 --> 00:04:33,880
Watch who?

85
00:04:36,480 --> 00:04:37,880
You're just talking nonsense.

86
00:04:37,880 --> 00:04:38,800
Take a good look at him.

87
00:04:39,440 --> 00:04:40,360
He'd be lucky

88
00:04:40,360 --> 00:04:42,559
if he could even stand up.

89
00:04:42,920 --> 00:04:44,360
How is he going to escape?

90
00:04:44,360 --> 00:04:47,119
He can't even sit up to eat.

91
00:04:49,840 --> 00:04:50,920
You're not looking at the reality.

92
00:04:51,800 --> 00:04:53,119
After what you did to him.

93
00:04:55,280 --> 00:04:56,760
Just talking nonsense.

94
00:05:07,000 --> 00:05:08,199
Aunt Tammy?

95
00:05:36,400 --> 00:05:37,239
Aunt Tammy?

96
00:05:53,719 --> 00:05:54,639
Where do you think you're going?!

97
00:05:56,199 --> 00:05:56,760
Come here!

98
00:05:58,000 --> 00:05:59,199
Just leave me alone!

99
00:06:02,400 --> 00:06:02,760
You maniac!

100
00:06:03,239 --> 00:06:04,039
Do you even realize it?

101
00:06:04,039 --> 00:06:04,639
You're completely insane!

102
00:06:05,119 --> 00:06:05,559
Bring it on.

103
00:06:07,079 --> 00:06:08,519
I'm not giving in to you this time.

104
00:06:08,719 --> 00:06:09,400
Someone like you

105
00:06:09,960 --> 00:06:10,880
do you even know how to fight?

106
00:06:11,599 --> 00:06:12,440
Try me and find out

107
00:06:13,840 --> 00:06:14,760
Listen to me.

108
00:06:15,519 --> 00:06:17,519
My brother and I were street kids.

109
00:06:17,800 --> 00:06:18,920
We've fought hundreds of people.

110
00:06:19,719 --> 00:06:20,599
We've taken plenty of beatings.

111
00:06:21,760 --> 00:06:22,519
But every single time

112
00:06:23,239 --> 00:06:25,119
we never let anyone
walk away in one piece.

113
00:06:26,039 --> 00:06:26,840
Come on.

114
00:06:26,840 --> 00:06:27,440
If you want to try

115
00:06:30,480 --> 00:06:30,840
Come on.

116
00:06:54,119 --> 00:06:55,679
I warned you

117
00:06:55,679 --> 00:06:57,239
Saturn.

118
00:06:59,760 --> 00:07:01,199
Madame mentioned

119
00:07:01,199 --> 00:07:02,199
that you're handling the case

120
00:07:02,199 --> 00:07:03,599
regarding Khun Saturn, right?

121
00:07:04,039 --> 00:07:05,519
Do you really not know

122
00:07:05,519 --> 00:07:07,119
where Khun Saturn disappeared to?

123
00:07:08,320 --> 00:07:10,199
I only handled the part

124
00:07:10,199 --> 00:07:11,599
about paying off the reporters.

125
00:07:11,599 --> 00:07:13,159
To stop them from digging
into the story about Khun Saturn

126
00:07:13,159 --> 00:07:14,920
and his boyfriend
who committed suicide.

127
00:07:14,920 --> 00:07:16,079
As for the disappearance

128
00:07:16,079 --> 00:07:17,360
of Venus and Saturn

129
00:07:17,639 --> 00:07:19,239
I have absolutely no idea about that.

130
00:07:20,960 --> 00:07:21,840
Is it possible

131
00:07:22,639 --> 00:07:24,639
that these events are connected?

132
00:07:25,159 --> 00:07:26,199
It's possible.

133
00:07:26,599 --> 00:07:27,760
I've been constantly
coordinating with the police

134
00:07:27,760 --> 00:07:28,920
who are working on the case.

135
00:07:29,559 --> 00:07:30,360
This whole thing

136
00:07:30,360 --> 00:07:32,519
might have more to it
than meets the eye.

137
00:07:33,960 --> 00:07:34,960
Do you think

138
00:07:35,559 --> 00:07:37,079
someone close to us

139
00:07:37,480 --> 00:07:38,719
might be involved in this?

140
00:07:39,159 --> 00:07:41,280
I can't jump to conclusions yet.

141
00:07:41,280 --> 00:07:41,719
But...

142
00:07:42,960 --> 00:07:45,679
anything is possible.

143
00:07:51,320 --> 00:07:52,079
Auntie.

144
00:07:52,280 --> 00:07:52,679
Yes?

145
00:07:53,719 --> 00:07:55,000
I've found the twins.

146
00:07:55,639 --> 00:07:55,960
Really?

147
00:07:55,960 --> 00:07:57,360
Where are my grandsons?

148
00:07:59,000 --> 00:07:59,760
Let's just say

149
00:07:59,760 --> 00:08:02,239
you should see for yourself, Auntie

150
00:08:03,400 --> 00:08:04,199
Here.

151
00:08:15,880 --> 00:08:19,239
It really is Saturn.

152
00:08:19,640 --> 00:08:20,000
Khae

153
00:08:20,000 --> 00:08:21,479
this isn't an old video, is it?

154
00:08:22,119 --> 00:08:23,000
Definitely not.

155
00:08:23,600 --> 00:08:24,800
A friend of mine

156
00:08:24,800 --> 00:08:26,199
just sent this

157
00:08:26,199 --> 00:08:27,399
fresh from Hong Kong.

158
00:08:27,960 --> 00:08:28,920
And

159
00:08:29,119 --> 00:08:30,079
there's more.

160
00:08:33,520 --> 00:08:35,039
Hello, Grandmother.

161
00:08:35,039 --> 00:08:36,880
Right now, I'm with Saturn.

162
00:08:36,880 --> 00:08:37,960
Don't worry about us.

163
00:08:37,960 --> 00:08:39,960
We're just taking some time to relax.

164
00:08:39,960 --> 00:08:40,720
Tomorrow,

165
00:08:40,720 --> 00:08:42,560
we're heading out to the desert.

166
00:08:42,560 --> 00:08:44,479
We're going to ride camels
and smoke shisha.

167
00:08:44,479 --> 00:08:45,399
We're going to

168
00:08:45,399 --> 00:08:46,800
party hard and go all out.

169
00:08:46,800 --> 00:08:49,640
Love you always, Grandmother. Mwah!

170
00:08:49,960 --> 00:08:50,520
Oh, dear.

171
00:08:51,239 --> 00:08:52,840
And here I was,
so worried about them.

172
00:08:53,239 --> 00:08:53,680
Turns out...

173
00:08:54,920 --> 00:08:56,000
Exactly.

174
00:08:56,000 --> 00:08:56,800
Are these really the people

175
00:08:57,239 --> 00:08:57,960
you're going

176
00:08:57,960 --> 00:08:59,560
to appoint as the top executives

177
00:08:59,560 --> 00:09:00,760
of the entire hotel chain?

178
00:09:01,239 --> 00:09:02,520
The business you
built from the ground up

179
00:09:02,520 --> 00:09:04,199
with so much hardship.

180
00:09:05,600 --> 00:09:06,000
Madame.

181
00:09:06,640 --> 00:09:07,359
I've figured out

182
00:09:07,920 --> 00:09:09,560
what happened to Khun Venus.

183
00:09:10,119 --> 00:09:11,239
Yes, I know.

184
00:09:11,239 --> 00:09:12,560
Khae already told me everything.

185
00:09:12,960 --> 00:09:14,000
Told you what, Madame?

186
00:09:14,880 --> 00:09:16,960
I told her exactly what kind of kid

187
00:09:17,840 --> 00:09:19,199
Auntie's precious grandson really is.

188
00:09:19,840 --> 00:09:21,479
Such an absolute good for nothing!

189
00:09:22,359 --> 00:09:24,760
On his grandmother's
milestone birthday

190
00:09:24,760 --> 00:09:26,119
the very day they were
supposed to be appointed

191
00:09:26,119 --> 00:09:28,399
as the top executives
of the hotel chain!

192
00:09:28,680 --> 00:09:29,760
Yet they only care about having fun

193
00:09:29,760 --> 00:09:31,239
and running off to party.

194
00:09:31,640 --> 00:09:33,319
Khun Khaeng Khae,
what are you talking about?

195
00:09:34,239 --> 00:09:34,880
I have proof.

196
00:09:35,600 --> 00:09:36,920
Yes, I've seen it all.

197
00:09:37,319 --> 00:09:38,239
Seen what, Madame?

198
00:09:41,800 --> 00:09:43,199
See for yourself.

199
00:09:48,880 --> 00:09:49,960
Madame.

200
00:09:49,960 --> 00:09:51,560
These clips are AI-generated.

201
00:09:52,199 --> 00:09:53,119
Khun Khaeng Khae.

202
00:09:53,319 --> 00:09:54,880
Stop spinning lies out of thin air.

203
00:09:55,079 --> 00:09:56,520
Adding fuel to the fire to
turn Madame against

204
00:09:56,520 --> 00:09:58,119
Khun Venus and Khun Saturn.

205
00:09:58,800 --> 00:09:59,760
Because the truth is, you...

206
00:09:59,760 --> 00:10:00,239
Enough!

207
00:10:00,840 --> 00:10:02,600
AI or whatever, I don't want to hear it!

208
00:10:02,840 --> 00:10:04,520
I raised my grandsons
with my own hands.

209
00:10:04,520 --> 00:10:06,119
I know exactly how they are.

210
00:10:06,119 --> 00:10:07,479
Especially Saturn.

211
00:10:07,960 --> 00:10:10,199
But Khun Venus isn't like that.

212
00:10:10,800 --> 00:10:12,880
Venus is gullible

213
00:10:12,880 --> 00:10:14,000
and easily influenced.

214
00:10:14,000 --> 00:10:16,199
It's no surprise he got
carried away and followed Saturn.

215
00:10:16,760 --> 00:10:18,840
They are brothers, twins even.

216
00:10:18,840 --> 00:10:20,159
They are practically the same person.

217
00:10:20,479 --> 00:10:20,960
But...

218
00:10:21,680 --> 00:10:22,199
Enough.

219
00:10:22,399 --> 00:10:23,960
I don't want to hear anything else.

220
00:10:24,680 --> 00:10:27,079
The grandsons I pinned all my hopes on

221
00:10:27,079 --> 00:10:28,760
to be my successors

222
00:10:29,560 --> 00:10:31,600
only care about fooling around,

223
00:10:31,600 --> 00:10:33,960
squandering the family fortune day by day.

224
00:10:40,800 --> 00:10:42,960
You really are unbelievable.

225
00:10:44,039 --> 00:10:45,720
You never listen to anything I say.

226
00:10:46,079 --> 00:10:46,520
And now look.

227
00:10:47,199 --> 00:10:49,039
What kind of demon possessed you

228
00:10:49,399 --> 00:10:51,479
to make you go and fight him?

229
00:10:51,479 --> 00:10:52,920
Throwing punches at him like that.

230
00:10:55,520 --> 00:10:58,239
Well, we both have two hands
and two feet, Auntie.

231
00:10:58,760 --> 00:10:59,479
How was I supposed to know

232
00:10:59,880 --> 00:11:01,319
he packs such a heavy punch?

233
00:11:01,920 --> 00:11:02,760
And see what happened?

234
00:11:03,239 --> 00:11:04,319
Actually, it's for the best.

235
00:11:04,920 --> 00:11:06,880
Letting him take all
his anger out on me.

236
00:11:07,720 --> 00:11:09,119
To make up for all the resentment he holds

237
00:11:10,880 --> 00:11:11,760
Aunt Tammy.

238
00:11:12,760 --> 00:11:13,880
Yeah, I know.

239
00:11:14,399 --> 00:11:15,159
Geez.

240
00:11:15,479 --> 00:11:17,319
I told myself I'd stay out of it.
I really did.

241
00:11:19,640 --> 00:11:20,520
But what can I do?

242
00:11:21,079 --> 00:11:22,239
This old woman's heart

243
00:11:22,239 --> 00:11:23,680
this withered heart

244
00:11:23,680 --> 00:11:25,239
just couldn't bear to watch.

245
00:11:28,239 --> 00:11:29,239
Where else does it hurt?

246
00:11:31,000 --> 00:11:32,520
You know what, apply the ointment yourself.

247
00:11:32,520 --> 00:11:33,119
I'm staying out of this.

248
00:11:33,960 --> 00:11:34,720
Before I end up getting hit too.

249
00:11:37,600 --> 00:11:38,439
Not getting involved.

250
00:11:54,720 --> 00:11:55,079
Here.

251
00:11:55,920 --> 00:11:56,479
Let me help.

252
00:12:00,119 --> 00:12:01,199
Be gentle.

253
00:12:08,880 --> 00:12:10,039
I said, be gentle!

254
00:12:10,039 --> 00:12:11,199
Does it hurt?

255
00:12:12,199 --> 00:12:13,239
Just a little.

256
00:12:13,520 --> 00:12:14,920
Your punch wasn't even
that heavy anyway......

257
00:12:18,199 --> 00:12:19,399
Oh, really? / Are you crazy?

258
00:12:19,840 --> 00:12:20,319
What are you laughing at?

259
00:12:21,000 --> 00:12:22,520
You punched me,
and you still have the nerve to laugh?
